page.title: 14FENDRAYTON BUILDINGS
page.content: {Fendrayton Church stands on the site of the church built before the {Conquest.}The first vicar was William De Godesdon.The date of presentation was 22nd February 1232. Across the road is an old house where{Mrs Warboys}(a typical old villager)lives.She has lived in the village for 40 years but she has lived in that particular house for 9 years as her other one burnt down. Her house is{Dutch.}When the Dutch people came to{drain the fens}they would live in it. Above the house is a sign which says{'1715 NIET ZONDER HRBYT'}(which means{'Nothing gained without labour') There is a{pub}on one corner of the village called{'The Three Tuns' which was built in 1799. There are more old houses than new ones,and most of the new ones are detatched.
